    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>The field of vaccination is witnessing a remarkable surge in the development of innovative strategies. There is a need to develop technological platforms capable of generating human data prior to progressing to clinical trials. Here we introduce VaxSkin, a flexible solution designed for the comprehensive monitoring of the natural human skin ecosystem\u2019s response to vaccines over time. Based on bioengineering to repurpose surgical resections, it allows a comprehensive analysis of the response to vaccines at both organ and single-cell levels. Upon injection of the mRNA-1273 COVID-19 vaccine, we characterized precise sequential molecular events triggered upon detection of the exogenous substance. We also found that the vaccine consistently targets DC/macrophages and mast cells, regardless of the administration route, while promoting specific cell-cell communications in surrounding immune cell subsets. Given its direct translational relevance, VaxSkin provides a multiscale vision of skin vaccination that could pave the way toward the development of new vaccination development strategies.</jats:p>",
